    category: 'culture',
    summary: 'An estimated 87% of classic games are commercially unavailable, and a significant proportion exist in no preserved form. Decaying magnetic media, proprietary formats, and copyright law that prevents archiving of commercial software have created a preservation crisis that the games industry has been slow to address. The organisations working to prevent this loss operate in legal grey areas that complicate even well-intentioned archival work.',
